[SN]TITLE[SN]
Burst fire hydrant soaks shoppers in Nottingham

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A fire hydrant showered shoppers with water when it burst, creating a 15m high fountain in a city centre.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
25 March 2015 Last updated at 12:25 GMT
It broke in Nottingham's Old Market Square, spraying a jet more than twice the height of a double-decker bus into the air.
The water also fell on buses and trams on Monday.
It was later repaired.
